  "texts": [
    "The estimated pitch and formant frequency were resampled to 125 Hz, the same as the ECoG signal and spectrogram sampling frequency.",
    "The mean square error between these speech parameters generated by the speech encoder and those estimated by the Praat method was used as a supervised reference loss, in addition to the unsupervised spectrogram reconstruction and STOI losses, making the training of the auto-encoder semi-supervised.",
    "Our speech synthesizer was inspired by the traditional speech vocoder, which generates speech by switching between voiced and unvoiced content, each generated by filtering a specific excitation signal.",
    "Instead of switching between the two components, we use a soft mix of the two components, making the speech synthesizer differentiable.",
    "This enables us to train the ECoG decoder and the speech encoder end-to-end by minimizing the spectrogram reconstruction loss with backpropagation."
  ],
